00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:17.900
Okay, what does self-servant identity mean in

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:18.680
a technical sense?

00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:22.240
As we understand it here in this AT-Proto context

00:03:22.240 --> 00:03:28.390
, it means that there is some public key infrastructure, which

00:03:28.860 --> 00:03:34.130
includes, which is the pointer, this common, some even

00:03:34.460 --> 00:03:39.110
call it source of truth, but I would advise against that

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:39.360
.

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.600
But it's a common reference point.

00:03:41.720 --> 00:03:47.460
You could even claim it's something like DNS, but there

00:03:47.460 --> 00:03:53.290
is just one domain, and it's not about renting human

00:03:53.410 --> 00:04:01.800
readable expressions, but being publicly available in a public database

00:04:01.830 --> 00:04:02.230
.

00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:04.340
So it's public keys.

00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:07.220
The public key infrastructure problem is very old.

00:04:07.220 --> 00:04:09.860
I think it's around 40 years old, I think,

00:04:09.910 --> 00:04:10.170
something like that.

00:04:10.240 --> 00:04:13.590
So maybe it's not really, you cannot really solve it

00:04:13.590 --> 00:04:13.800
.

00:04:13.800 --> 00:04:19.920
You can just make several evolutionary progress steps there.

00:04:19.920 --> 00:04:24.720
Yeah, so the idea is that you have an identifier,

00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:30.290
which there is a clear open-defined method, can be

00:04:30.900 --> 00:04:34.740
resolved to a document that includes all kinds of metadata about this

00:04:34.740 --> 00:04:36.100
DIT subject.

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:39.230
And this all works only if we have, if you can

00:04:39.230 --> 00:04:41.710
maintain this common verifiable data registry.

00:04:41.720 --> 00:04:46.850
So I was hooked because I understood from Marko's descriptions

00:04:46.860 --> 00:04:53.230
that if systems start to use these kinds of identity systems underneath

00:04:53.600 --> 00:05:00.960
everything, in a wider sense, the role of the identity

00:05:00.960 --> 00:05:03.400
