00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:50.640
So a little bit technical again.

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:55.290
Self-sovereign account creation means you sign a block

00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:58.790
of a string of elements.

00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:00.220
You sign it yourself.

00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:01.740
And then you hash it.

00:08:01.880 --> 00:08:03.100
And then you truncate it.

00:08:03.120 --> 00:08:04.280
And then this becomes your DID.

00:08:04.520 --> 00:08:08.440
And the message is you can do this on your own.

00:08:08.440 --> 00:08:11.390
And then you broadcast this more or less to the outside world

00:08:11.540 --> 00:08:14.200
and hope that the outside world remembers this in a coherent fashion

00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:14.400
.

00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:17.380
So this is really kind of radical.

00:08:17.380 --> 00:08:21.640
And I, back in 2016, I could not understand which

00:08:21.640 --> 00:08:25.940
company, I thought in company terms, which company would ever

00:08:26.030 --> 00:08:28.320
apply this because they're, in a sense, giving away

00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:29.970
the crown jewels right from the start.

00:08:30.640 --> 00:08:33.380
So what would be the business incentive to do that?

00:08:33.390 --> 00:08:34.770
Or something like, I could not make sense of it.

00:08:34.780 --> 00:08:39.920
And now I finally understand, okay, there is a way

00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:43.950
because actually now it's out there.

00:08:43.960 --> 00:08:47.540
Technical details about the DID document.

00:08:47.660 --> 00:08:48.720
So I will skip right now.

00:08:48.720 --> 00:08:53.450
What I will say is that this concept means that you,

00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:58.500
by signing and hashing these things, you are adding,

00:08:58.510 --> 00:09:02.580
it's like a meta-paradigmatic rationality

00:09:02.580 --> 00:09:04.100
in some sense.

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:08.450
You say, it's the only thing we care, is

00:09:08.450 --> 00:09:14.160
the signature correct and is the hashing matching?

00:09:14.180 --> 00:09:17.020
So these are mathematical functions.

00:09:17.120 --> 00:09:19.340
There is no, I would suggest there is, it's

00:09:19.340 --> 00:09:21.360
hard to put some politics into them.

00:09:21.360 --> 00:09:23.860
It's kind of, yeah.

00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:28.720
It goes back to the formulation that I've heard is that

00:09:28.720 --> 00:09:32.800
the cypherpunks, a movement that I observed

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.190
, like many of you, I guess.

00:09:35.220 --> 00:09:38.710
And one of the slogans was, no army or no

00:09:38.710 --> 00:09:43.580
nation state actor, even the biggest sort of, the one

00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:47.100
equipped with the biggest arsenal of nuclear weapons.

00:09:47.120 --> 00:09:52.330
So this is a big claim that you say, okay,

00:09:52.840 --> 00:09:57.390
really, if we add this coherence, if we add

00:09:57.390 --> 00:10:01.010
this mathematics to all our power structures, this has some consequences

00:10:01.010 --> 00:10:01.200
.

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:04.790
And I think this is the original cypherpunks

00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:05.600
motto.

00:10:05.600 --> 00:10:08.970
And here in our project here, it means that if the

00:10:08.970 --> 00:10:14.260
PLC directory fundamentally changes its behavior in not doing that anymore

00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:19.240
, we all know that the project is dead in some sense

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:19.660
.

00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:24.780
Because this is the core, in my understanding, this is

00:10:24.880 --> 00:10:31.080
one of the core elements that enables these locking open methods.

00:10:31.080 --> 00:10:33.320
This is the same as if the master.

00:10:33.440 --> 00:10:37.580
social admin, which is the supernova in the ecosystem still

00:10:37.590 --> 00:10:41.660
, if the supernova turns off the migration or federation

00:10:41.690 --> 00:10:44.090
APIs, you know that this project, or at least the

00:10:44.120 --> 00:10:47.460
group that runs this instance, is politically also dead in some

00:10:47.460 --> 00:10:48.000
sense.

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:49.760
So it does not keep the core promise anymore.

00:10:50.320 --> 00:10:54.070
So I'm claiming that this is a political program that's

00:10:54.070 --> 00:10:57.250
now being sort of, or it's now emerging in some

00:10:57.250 --> 00:10:58.010
sense.

00:10:58.020 --> 00:11:00.960
And it says we don't need identity providers anymore.

00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:06.200
Very much in line with Article 1 of the Universal Declaration.

00:11:06.920 --> 00:11:08.870
So I'm claiming that the toothpaste is out.

00:11:08.880 --> 00:11:11.730
You cannot put it back in anymore because now a successful project

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:12.950
is actually using this.

00:11:12.960 --> 00:11:15.860
Marcos Sabadello, who has an overview of all

00:11:15.860 --> 00:11:18.970
the SSI systems, says, to his knowledge also,

00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:22.930
this AT-Protor ecosystem is the biggest emerging phenomenon

00:11:22.930 --> 00:11:25.050
that adopts this principle.

00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:28.030
And it's even if the PLC crashes and burns in

00:11:28.350 --> 00:11:32.350
one hour from now, we all understand that this idea makes

00:11:32.350 --> 00:11:35.620
sense and that we will keep working on it.

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:42.070
I could say a few things about the DRD method situation

00:11:42.070 --> 00:11:42.520
.

00:11:42.520 --> 00:11:46.910
So currently, PLC is the method being adopted and supported

00:11:46.930 --> 00:11:47.260
.

00:11:47.260 --> 00:11:50.060
There are, of course, this will never end, I

00:11:50.090 --> 00:11:50.760
think.

00:11:50.760 --> 00:11:55.900
This is something, this is an ongoing process where we debate

00:11:55.940 --> 00:12:00.740
about what are the best methods to achieve all what we want

00:12:00.750 --> 00:12:01.140
.

00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:06.220
For example, currently, there is something called SCID,

00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:09.840
which adds to the PLC concept a format, a pre

